任务按计划在[[协调世界时|协调世界时]]4月11日19点13分点火，第二级火箭发生异常，中央发动机（内侧）提前约两分钟熄火<ref name="lver">{{cite book | title = Saturn 5 Launch Vehicle Flight Evaluation Report: AS-508 Apollo 13 Mission | url = https://archive.org/details/nasa_techdoc_19900066486 | access-date = 2021-02-09 | date = 1970-06-20 | work = [[馬歇爾太空飛行中心|George C. Marshall Space Flight Center]] | publisher = NASA | location = Huntsville, Alabama | id = MPR-SAT-FE-70-2}}</ref><ref name="Benson-Faherty-1979">{{cite book | access-date = 2021-02-09 | url = https://ntrs.nasa.gov/api/citations/19790003956/downloads/19790003956.pdf | website = NASA | title = Moonport: A History of Apollo Launch Facilities and Operations | first = Charles D. | last = Benson | first2 = William Barnaby | last2 = Faherty | year = 1978 | location = Washington, D.C. | series = NASA History Series | id = SP-4204 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191212170117/https://ntrs.nasa.gov/archive/nasa/casi.ntrs.nasa.gov/19790003956.pdf | archive-date = 2019-12-12 | dead-url = no | format = PDF}}</ref>{{rp|494–499}}。异常是由严重的[[纵向耦合振动|纵向耦合振动]]导致，从阿波罗十号开始，土星五号运载火箭的制导系统会在发动机腔室压力偏移时自动关闭发动机<ref name="Larsen-2008">{{cite conference | title = NASA Experience with Pogo in Human Spaceflight Vehicles | url = https://ntrs.nasa.gov/api/citations/20080018689/downloads/20080018689.pdf | conference = NATO RTO Symposium ATV-152 on Limit-Cycle Oscillations and Other Amplitude-Limited, Self-Excited Vibrations | location = Norway | last = Larsen | first = Curtis E. | website = NASA Johnson Space Center | date = 2008-05-22 | id = RTO-MP-AVT-152 | access-date = 2021-02-09 | archive-date = 2020-07-28 | format = PDF | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200728234832/https://ntrs.nasa.gov/archive/nasa/casi.ntrs.nasa.gov/20080018689.pdf}}</ref>{{rp|5-13}}。双子座计划使用的[[泰坦系列運載火箭|泰坦系列運載火箭]]和过去阿波罗计划的运载火箭都曾发生纵向耦合振动<ref>{{cite journal | last = Fenwick | first = Jim | archive-date = 2009-01-13 | date = Spring 1992 | title = Pogo | url = http://www.engineeringatboeing.com/articles/pogo.htm | journal = Threshold | publisher = [[洛克达因公司|Pratt & Whitney Rocketdyne]] | access-date = 2009-01-13 | dead-url = yes | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090113180241/http://www.engineeringatboeing.com/articles/pogo.htm}}</ref><ref name="Larsen-2008" />{{rp|5-7–5-12}}，但阿波罗13号因与涡轮泵[[空穴現象|空穴現象]]相互影响变得特别严重<ref>{{cite journal | last = Dotson | first = Kirk | date = Winter 2003–2004 | title = Mitigating Pogo on Liquid-Fueled Rockets | journal = Crosslink | volume = 5 | issue = 1 | pages = 26–29 | location = El Segundo, California | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210114124216/http://aerospace.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/crosslink/V5N1.pdf | publisher = The Aerospace Corporation | access-date = 2021-02-09 | archive-date = 2021-01-14 | url = http://aerospace.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/crosslink/V5N1.pdf | dead-url = no | format = PDF}}</ref><ref name="launch">{{cite web | url = https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/01launch_ascent.html | title = Launch and Reaching Earth Orbit | year = 2016 | editor-last = Woods | editor-first = W. David | editor-last2 = Turhanov | editor-first2 = Alexandr | editor-last3 = Waugh | editor-first3 = Lennox J. | work = Apollo 13 Flight Journal | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201111211356/https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/01launch_ascent.html | dead-url = no | publisher = NASA | access-date = 2021-02-09 | archive-date = 2020-11-12}}</ref>。航空航天局本来有办法解决上述故障，但因时间太紧未能在阿波罗13号的运载火箭落实<ref name="Larsen-2008" />{{rp|5-13}}<ref>{{cite journal | title = 13 things that saved Apollo 13, Part 5: Unexplained shutdown of the Saturn V center engine | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210125002750/https://www.universetoday.com/62672/13-things-that-saved-apollo-13-part-5-unexplained-shutdown-of-the-saturn-v-center-engine/ | access-date = 2021-02-09 | archive-date = 2021-01-25 | url = https://www.universetoday.com/62672/13-things-that-saved-apollo-13-part-5-unexplained-shutdown-of-the-saturn-v-center-engine/ | last = Atkinson | first = Nancy | date = 2010-04-14 | journal = Universe Today | dead-url = no}}</ref>。事后调查表明中央发动机距发生灾难事故只差一个运转周期<ref name="Larsen-2008" />{{rp|5-13}}。中央发动机关闭后，外侧的四个发动机和[[S-IVB|第三级火箭]]的燃烧时间更长，基本足以补偿动力损失，火箭距190公里高空的预定圆形[[停泊轨道|停泊轨道]]非常近，并在约两小时后切入地月转移轨道，准备前往月球<ref name="lver" /><ref name="Benson-Faherty-1979" />{{rp|494–499}}。

阿波罗13号切入地月转移轨道后，斯威格特先分离和换位，把服务与指令舱“奥德赛”号和登月舱“宝瓶”号对接，再将太空船与第三级火箭分离<ref name="journal extraction">{{cite web | work = Apollo Lunar Flight Journal | url = https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/03tde.html | title = Day 1: Transposition, Docking and Extraction | date = 2017-02-17 | access-date = 2021-02-09 | last1 = Woods | first1 = W. David | last2 = Kemppanen | first2 = Johannes | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201111211356/https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/01launch_ascent.html | archive-date = 2020-11-11 | last3 = Turhanov | first3 = Alexander | last4 = Waugh | first4 = Lennox J. | dead-url = no}}</ref>。地面控制人员接下来控制第三级火箭朝阿波罗12号留下的地震仪范围撞击月球，撞击时间是在阿波罗13号计划启动正好三天后<ref name="Orloff-Harland-2006" />{{rp|367}}。

宇航员设定航天器花三天时间飞往弗拉·毛罗高地。任务启动30小时40分50秒，乘组在电视镜头前点火，将阿波罗13号送入混合轨道。航天器离开[[自由返回轨道|自由返回轨道]]，这也意味着如果发动机不能再度点火，航天器就无法自主返回地球。<ref name="journal midcourse">{{cite web | work = Apollo Lunar Flight Journal | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200811095854/https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/05day2-mcc2-tv.html | dead-url = no | url = https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/05day2-mcc2-tv.html | title = Day 2: Midcourse correction 2 on TV | date = 2017-02-17 | access-date = 2021-02-09 | archive-date = 2020-08-11}}</ref>航天器经自由返回轨道只能在月球赤道附近着陆，航天器切入地月转移轨道后可以随时进入混合轨道，这样就能从包括弗拉·毛罗高地在内的高纬度地点登月<ref name="journal hybrid">{{cite web | work = Apollo Lunar Flight Journal | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201101130233/https://history.nasa.gov/afj/launchwindow/lw1.html | archive-date = 2020-11-01 | url = https://history.nasa.gov/afj/launchwindow/lw1.html | title = Apollo lunar landing launch window: The controlling factors and constraints | year = 2009 | access-date = 2021-02-09 | author = Robin Wheeler}}</ref>。通话期间，斯威格特突然想起因日程繁忙，他忘记在4月15日最后期限前填写[[1040表格|联邦个人所得税申报表]]，通信马上变得热烈起来，他在任务控制人员的笑声中询问如何取得延期。最后斯威格特因“出国”获60天延期。<ref name="NASA-1970" />{{rp|8}}

根据计划，乘组需在火箭点火58小时后进入登月舱检测各项功能。宇航员在任务第三天醒来时，地面控制人员通知他们提前三小时开始，之后又提前一小时。任务开始55小时是预定的电视直播时间，洛弗尔充当司仪向观众介绍“奥德赛”与“宝瓶”内部景观。<ref name="storm">{{cite web | access-date = 2021-02-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200811103846/https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/07day3-before-the-storm.html | url = https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/07day3-before-the-storm.html | title = Day 3: Before the storm | year = 2016 | editor-last = Woods | editor-first = W. David | editor-last2 = Turhanov | editor-first2 = Alexandr | editor-last3 = Waugh | editor-first3 = Lennox J. | work = Apollo 13 Flight Journal | publisher = NASA | archive-date = 2020-08-11 | dead-url = no}}</ref>但美国电视网均未直播，阿波罗13号的演出没多少观众<ref name="Houston-Heflin-Aaron-2015">{{cite book | last = Houston | first = Rick | last2 = Heflin | first2 = J. Milt | last3 = Aaron | first3 = John | title = Go, Flight!: the Unsung Heroes of Mission Control, 1965–1992 | year = 2015 | publisher = University of Nebraska Press | edition = eBook | location = Lincoln, Nebraska | isbn = 978-0-8032-8494-4}}</ref>{{rp|206}}，洛弗尔的夫人玛丽莲前往任务控制中心贵宾室才能看到丈夫和队友<ref name="Chaikin-1998" />{{rp|285–287}}。

=== 事故 ===
火箭起飞近56小时、电视直播结束约六分半钟后，阿波罗13号距地约33万公里<ref name="journal Houston">{{cite web | work = Apollo Lunar Flight Journal | first3 = Alexander | last4 = Waugh | first4 = Lennox J. | url = https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/08day3-problem.html | title = Day 3: 'Houston, we've had a problem' | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201212183613/https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/08day3-problem.html | dead-url = no | date = 2017-05-30 | access-date = 2021-02-09 | last1 = Woods | first1 = W. David | last2 = Kemppanen | first2 = Johannes | last3 = Turhanov | archive-date = 2020-12-12}}</ref>。海斯此时完成功能检查正在关闭登月舱，洛弗尔收起电视摄像头，通信员[[杰克·洛斯马|杰克·洛斯马]]向斯威格特发出指令，其中包括调整航天器[[定向_(幾何)|姿态]]，以便拍摄[[班尼特彗星|班尼特彗星]]的照片<ref name="journal Houston" /><ref name="Chaikin-1998" />{{rp|292}}。

服务舱氧气瓶的压力传感器此前似乎有故障，负责监控服务与指令舱电气系统的电气、环境与耗材主任西摩·李伯格要求启动罐内搅拌风扇。氧气瓶内风扇通常每天都会启动，确保罐内气流和温度更均匀，压力读数更准确。<ref name="journal Houston" />飞行指导克兰兹要求李伯格过几分钟再启动，等待电视直播后宇航员收尾<ref name="Houston-Heflin-Aaron-2015" />{{rp|207}}，接下来洛斯马把要求传达给斯威格特，后者打开风扇开关并在数秒钟后关闭<ref name="journal Houston" /><ref name="Chaikin-1998" />{{rp|292}}。
{{Listen|filename=Apollo13-wehaveaproblem.ogg|title=休斯顿，我们遇上麻烦|description=1970年4月14日，斯威格特与洛弗尔汇报事故（2分59秒）《休斯顿，我们遇上麻烦》|format=[[Ogg|Ogg]]}}

斯威格特打开开关95秒后<ref name="Houston-Heflin-Aaron-2015" />{{rp|207}}，宇航员听到“巨响”，同时电力显著波动，航天器姿态控制推进器点火<ref name="Orloff-Harland-2006" />{{rp|368}}<ref name="Orloff-2000" />{{rp|152–157}}。与地球的通信和遥测中断1.8秒，直到系统自动把[[定向天线|高增益]][[统一S波段|S波段]]天线从窄波束模式切换至宽波束模式<ref name="Accident report" />{{rp|4-44}}。事故发生在[[协调世界时|UTC]]4月14日凌晨3点8分，火箭点火55小时54分53秒。斯威格特在26秒后汇报：“[[休斯顿，我们遇上麻烦|休斯顿，我们遇上麻烦]]”，洛弗尔的声音也在任务启动55小时55分42秒时响起：“休斯顿，我们遇上麻烦。主电路B电压不足。”<ref name="journal Houston" />

洛弗尔本以为巨响是海斯启动登月舱增压阀所致（海斯经常这样吓唬队友），但马上看出海斯根本不知道怎么回事。斯威格特以为是[[流星体|流星体]]撞上登月舱，但他和洛弗尔很快就确定没有漏气情况。<ref name="Chaikin-1998" />{{rp|293}}服务舱有两个配电系统，服务与指令舱几乎所有功能都需电力驱动。“主电路B电压不足”表明服务舱三个[[燃料电池|燃料电池]]无法向第二个配电系统提供充足[[電壓|電壓]]，这些电池是从液氢和液氧罐抽取气体燃烧产生电能。主电路B一度恢复正常，但很快主电路A和B的电压都偏低。海斯检查时发现三个燃料电池有两个没电，根据任务守则，所有燃料电池都正常才能进入月球轨道。<ref name="Chaikin-1998" />{{rp|293–294}}

众多读数在事故发生后几分钟内出现异常，显示二号罐已空，一号罐气压缓慢下降，[[阿波罗制导计算机|航天器上的计算机]]重启，高增益天线不起作用。李伯格事故前集中关注一号罐，认为一号罐的读数对二号罐很有参考价值，没发现二号罐搅拌后的危险信号，支持大厅任务控制人员当时同意他的看法。面对克兰兹的质疑，李伯格一度表示仪器问题可能导致读数错误，此后多年他人都以此取笑李伯格。<ref name="Cass 1" />洛弗尔看向窗外并汇报，太空船正朝太空排放“某种气体”，表明肯定发生重大故障<ref name="Houston-Heflin-Aaron-2015" />{{rp|215}}。

燃料电池需要氧气才能工作，所以电池都会在一号液氧罐耗尽时失效，服务与指令舱此后完全要靠指令舱蓄电池与氧气“调压罐”供电和供氧。指令舱蓄电池和供氧在返航阶段的作用无可替代，但剩余燃料电池已耗尽液氧罐的氧，开始消耗调压罐。克兰兹下令隔断调压罐节省氧气，但这就意味着燃料电池会在两小时内没电。<ref name="Chaikin-1998" />{{rp|293–294}}航天器周围空间到处是事故产生的小碎片，加大利用恒星导航的难度<ref name="Chaikin-1998" />{{rp|299}}。原有任务目标全部放弃，变成确保宇航员活着回到地球<ref name="Cass 2">{{cite web | last = Cass | first = Stephen | title = Houston, we have a solution, part 2 | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200804200652/https://spectrum.ieee.org/tech-history/space-age/apollo-13-we-have-a-solution-part-2 | url = https://spectrum.ieee.org/tech-history/space-age/apollo-13-we-have-a-solution-part-2 | archive-date = 2020-08-04 | date = 2005-04-01 | website = IEEE | access-date = 2021-02-09}}</ref>。

=== 绕月旋转 ===
[[File:Direct_Abort_Trajectory_-_Lunar_Landing_Symposium,_MSC_Jun66.jpg|upright=1.2]]
[[File:NASA-Apollo13-ViewsOfMoon-20200224.webm|thumb]]資料繪製的阿波罗13号任务所見之月球景观（2分24秒）]]

为满足月表作业需要，登月舱配有充满电的电池和装满氧气的气罐，克兰兹要求宇航员启动登月舱充当“救生艇”<ref name="Cass 1" />，这种手段过去曾有设想，但当时认为不大可能需要<ref name="Lovell-Kluger-2000" />{{rp|83–87}}。阿波罗十号训练模拟指令舱泄露后如何利用登月舱存活，当时登月舱开机时间太长，飞行控制人员于是制定紧急操作程序<ref name="Cass 2" />。如果阿波罗13号的事故发生在返程阶段，登月舱已经弃置，宇航员就无法生还<ref name="LM-ALSEP">{{cite web | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201019204208/https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/nmc/spacecraft/display.action?id=1970-029C | url = https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/nmc/spacecraft/display.action?id=1970-029C | title = Apollo 13 Lunar Module/ALSEP | website = NASA Space Science Data Coordinated Archive | access-date = 2021-02-09 | archive-date = 2020-10-19 | dead-url = no}}</ref>；或是登月舱降落月表，洛弗尔和海斯在月表作业，服务与指令舱在月球轨道爆炸，宇航员同样无法生还<ref name="Yahoo 50th">{{cite news | publisher = [[雅虎新闻|Yahoo! News]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200726070317/https://news.yahoo.com/houston-ve-had-problem-remembering-050652323.html | url = https://news.yahoo.com/houston-ve-had-problem-remembering-050652323.html | access-date = 2021-02-09 | date = 2020-04-09 | title = 'Houston, we've had a problem': Remembering Apollo 13 at 50 | last = Dunn | first = Marcia | agency = Associated Press | archive-date = 2020-07-26 | dead-url = no}}</ref>。

为确保宇航员安全返回，路线选择至关重要。如果采用“直接中止”机制，在抵达月球前用服务舱主发动机（服务推进系统）返回，那么不但要确保服务推进系统没有因事故受损，而且燃料电池必须继续供电至少一小时才能满足功率要求。克兰兹决定迂回：航天器先绕月球旋转，转到朝地球方向时再返航。事故发生时，阿波罗13号位于混合轨道，准备前往弗拉·毛罗高地，如今需要回到自由返回轨道。登月舱的[[下降级推进系统|下降级推进系统]]虽不及服务推进系统强劲，但足以完成上述任务。不过，任务规划从未考虑在登月舱操控服务与指令舱，所以需要技术人员在任务控制中心的计算机上编写新软件。洛弗尔关闭指令舱时抄下制导系统方向信息，经过笔算输入登月舱制导系统。接下来任务控制中心根据宇航员要求检查数据，登月舱导航计算机尚处关机状态。<ref name="Cass 2" /><ref name="Chaikin-1998" />{{rp|297–298}}任务启动61小时29分43.49秒，下降级推进系统点火34.23秒，将阿波罗13号带回自由返回轨道<ref name="Orloff-Harland-2006" />{{rp|369}}。
[[File:Mare_Moscoviense_AS13-60-8648.jpg|thumb]]外的月球照片]]

经过上述调整，阿波罗13号还需约四天才能返回地球并溅落[[印度洋|印度洋]]，但航空航天局在印度洋的搜救实力不足。杰里·博斯蒂克等飞行动力官员忧心忡忡，既想缩短时间，又希望能把溅落地点移到大部分搜救部队所在的[[太平洋|太平洋]]。第一种方案能节省36小时，但需抛弃服务舱，导致指令舱防热大底返程期间在太空暴露，任务规划时从未设想这种情况。飞行动力官员还提出其他方案。航空航天局官员和工程师开会研讨后，现场资深人员、[[林登·约翰逊太空中心|载人航天中心]]主任[[罗伯特·吉鲁斯|罗伯特·吉鲁斯]]决定用下降级推进系统点火，节省12小时并溅落太平洋。此次点火计划在航天器抵达[[绕月轨道|近月点]]（绕月轨道距月球最近的位置）两小时后开始。<ref name="Cass 2" />据《[[吉尼斯世界纪录|吉尼斯世界纪录]]》所述，阿波罗13号在近月点创下载人航天器绝对高度纪录并保持至今：{{lang|en|UTC}}4月15日0点21分，离地40万零171公里<ref>{{cite book | editor-last = Glenday | editor-first = Craig | title = Guinness World Records 2010 | year = 2010 | publisher = Bantam Books | location = New York | isbn = 978-0-553-59337-2 | page = 13 | access-date = 2021-02-09 | url = https://archive.org/details/guinnessworldrec00vari/page/13}}</ref>{{refn|group="注"|月球在阿波罗13号任务期间靠近[[拱點|距地球最远的轨道位置]]，所以才能创下上述纪录。阿波罗13号采用独特的自由返回轨道，所以比[[月球背面|月球背面]]还要远约100公里，比其他阿波罗登月任务都远，不过即便没有这100公里，最高纪录仍属阿波罗13号。<ref name="Adamo-2009">{{cite magazine | title = The Elusive Human Maximum Altitude Record | last = Adamo | first = Daniel | magazine = Quest: The History of Spaceflight Quarterly | volume = 16 | issue = 4 | year = 2009 | issn = 1065-7738}}</ref>{{rp|37}}天体动力学家丹尼尔·阿达莫2009年重建轨迹后将纪录数据定在{{lang|en|UTC}}0点34分13秒，40万零46公里。阿波罗十号以39万9806公里紧随其后。<ref name="Adamo-2009" />{{rp|41}}}}。

等待下降级推进系统点火期间，三人得知第三级火箭正如计划的那样撞击月球，洛弗尔自嘲：“好吧，至少此次飞行不至一事无成”<ref name="journal leaving" /><ref>{{cite book | last = Cooper | first = Henry S. F. Jr. | title = Thirteen: The Apollo Mission that Failed | orig-year = 1972 | year = 2013 | publisher = Open Road Integrated Media, Inc. | location = New York | isbn = 978-1-4804-6221-2 | pages = 84–86}}</ref>。克兰兹领导的白队任务控制人员大部分时间花在协助其他队伍并制订保障宇航员返航急需规程，此次点火也由他们操控<ref name="Houston-Heflin-Aaron-2015" />{{rp|221–222}}。正常情况下，只需把洛弗尔输入登月舱计算机的数据对应宇航员用于导航的恒星位置就能精确把握点火时间，但航天器周围飘浮的大量闪光碎片导致这根本不可能。宇航员最后采用不会与碎片混淆的太阳导航。休斯顿告知三人，点火时月球是在登月舱指令长窗口正中，每秒误差不到0.3米。<ref name="journal leaving" />任务启动79小时27分38.95秒，下降级推进系统点火并持续4分23秒<ref name="Orloff-Harland-2006" />{{rp|391}}，宇航员接下来关闭登月舱大部分系统节省资源<ref name="journal leaving">{{cite web | work = Apollo Lunar Flight Journal | access-date = 2021-02-10 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200811101536/https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/13day4-leaving-moon.html | dead-url = no | url = https://history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/13day4-leaving-moon.html | title = Day 4: Leaving the Moon | archive-date = 2020-08-11 | date = 2017-02-17}}</ref>。

=== 返回地球 ===
[[File:Apollo13_apparatus.jpg|thumb]]罐]]

登月舱氧气充足，但仍需解决二氧化碳吸收器效能不足的问题。这种仪器的工作原理是用[[氢氧化锂|氢氧化锂]]颗粒罐吸收二氧化碳，登月舱的吸收器是按两名宇航员在月球停留45小时设计，不足以保障三名宇航员返回地球所需。<ref name="Houston-Heflin-Aaron-2015" />{{rp|224}}指令舱的氢氧化锂颗粒罐充足，但形状和尺寸都与登月舱设备不符。地面工程师提出多种方案弥合差距，如利用塑料、操作手册封面，胶带等。<ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.newspapers.com/clip/36237422/astronauts-beat-air-crisis-by/ | title = Astronauts Beat Air Crisis By Do-It-Yourself Gadget | newspaper = Detroit Free Press | location = Detroit, Michigan | date = 1970-04-16 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200815084218/https://www.newspapers.com/clip/36237422/astronauts-beat-air-crisis-by/ | archive-date = 2020-08-15 | page = 12–C | last = Pothier | first = Richard | via = Newspapers.com | dead-url = no | access-date = 2021-02-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | last1 = Barell | first1 = John | title = Antarctic Adventures: Life Lessons from Polar Explorers | publisher = Balboa Press | isbn = 978-1-5043-6651-9 | access-date = 2021-02-10 | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=yJiaDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT154&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false | page = 154 | year = 2016 | archive-date = 2021-05-03 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210503044620/https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=yJiaDQAAQBAJ&pg=PT154&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q&f=false | dead-url = no }}</ref>航空航天局工程师把临时改造的设备称作“邮箱”。航天器通讯员[[约瑟夫·科文|约瑟夫·科文]]花费一小时将制造方法念给乘组，洛弗尔与海斯制作“邮箱”，效果立竿见影，二氧化碳含量马上下降。洛弗尔称，此次临时改造堪称“地面与太空合作典范”。<ref name="Cortright-1975">{{cite book | last = Lovell | first = James A. | editor-last = Cortright | editor-first = Edgar M. | title = Apollo Expeditions to the Moon | access-date = 2021-02-10 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200108230349/https://ntrs.nasa.gov/archive/nasa/casi.ntrs.nasa.gov/19760005868.pdf | url = https://ntrs.nasa.gov/api/citations/19760005868/downloads/19760005868.pdf | year = 1975 | publisher = NASA | location = Washington, D.C. | id = SP-350 | chapter = Chapter 13: "Houston, We've Had a Problem" | dead-url = no | format = PDF | archive-date = 2020-01-08}}}</ref>{{rp|257–262}}
[[File:Apollo_13_Hasselblad_image_from_film_magazine_62-JJ_(cropped).jpg|thumb]]

燃料电池为服务与指令舱供电时能生成水，但登月舱用的是不产生水的[[氧化銀電池|银锌电池]]，不但电力有限，设备冷却和维持生命必须的水也很紧张，宇航员把登月舱能耗降至最低<ref name="Mission-Operations-Report-1970" />{{rp|III‑17, III-33, III-40}}。斯威格特从指令舱水龙头接满几个饮用水袋<ref name="journal leaving" />，但据海斯初步计算，即使各人按比例限量用水，航天器再入前五小时就会没有冷却用水。考虑到阿波罗11号登月舱在月球轨道抛弃后虽然没水，但仍能继续工作七到八小时，所以再入前五小时没水应该不会影响宇航员生存，最后阿波罗13号溅落时还剩12.8公斤水。<ref name="Cortright-1975" />{{rp|254–257}}每名宇航员每天的用水额度仅0.2升，三人一共瘦下来14公斤，海斯还患上[[泌尿道感染|尿道感染]]<ref name="mission summary">{{cite web | last = Jones | first = Eric M. | date = 2006-01-04 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200811095804/https://history.nasa.gov/alsj/a13/a13.summary.html | dead-url = no | url = https://history.nasa.gov/alsj/a13/a13.summary.html | title = The frustrations of Fra Mauro: Part I | work = Apollo Lunar Surface Journal | access-date = 2021-02-10 | archive-date = 2020-08-11}}</ref><ref name="Cortright-1975" />{{rp|262–263}}。海斯的病情可能是因饮水太少所致，同时微重力和宇宙辐射可能削弱免疫系统对病原体的抵抗力<ref>{{cite journal | last = Kennedy | first = A.R. | year = 2014 | title = Biological effects of space radiation and development of effective countermeasures | journal = Life Sciences in Space Research | volume = 1 | issue = 1 | pages = 10–43 | doi = 10.1016/j.lssr.2014.02.004 | pmid = 25258703 | pmc = 4170231}}</ref>。
[[File:Apollo_13_Houston,_We've_Got_a_Problem.ogv|thumb]]

黑暗的航天器内气温低至3°C，洛弗尔一度考虑三人穿上航天服，但又担心这样太热。最后洛弗尔与海斯套上登月靴，斯威格特多穿一件外套。三人都很冷，特别是用水袋装水时把脚弄湿的斯威格特，而且他不用登月，所以没有登月靴。为避免影响航道，他们不能向太空排尿，所以只能把尿装在袋子里。水滴在墙上凝结，设备面板背面也可能有冷凝水，<ref name="Cortright-1975" />{{rp|257–263}}但这些水没有引起故障，估计[[阿波罗1号|阿波罗1号]]事故后的大量电力绝缘改进功不可没<ref>{{cite web | access-date = 2021-02-10 | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201121202055/https://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/constellation/main/A13_panel.html | url = https://www.nasa.gov/mission_pages/constellation/main/A13_panel.html | title = Generation Constellation Learns about Apollo 13 | last = Siceloff | first = Steven | date = 2007-09-20 | work = [[星座计划|Constellation Program]] | publisher = NASA | archive-date = 2020-11-21}}</ref>。面对重重困难，三名宇航员基本没有表达不快<ref name="Cass 3">{{cite web | last = Cass | first = Stephen | title = Houston, we have a solution, part 3 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210109150206/https://spectrum.ieee.org/tech-history/space-age/apollo-13-we-have-a-solution-part-3 | url = https://spectrum.ieee.org/tech-history/space-age/apollo-13-we-have-a-solution-part-3 | dead-url = no | date = 2005-04-01 | website = IEEE | access-date = 2021-02-10 | archive-date = 2021-01-09}}</ref>。

飞行控制员[[约翰·亚伦|约翰·亚伦]]与马丁利及众多工程师和设计师设计规程，将完全关闭的指令舱启动，此前还在飞行的指令舱从未彻底关闭后再通电启动，更不用说还是电力和时间都很紧张的阿波罗13号<ref>{{cite journal | last = Leopold | first = George | date = 2009-03-17 | title = Power engineer: Video interview with Apollo astronaut Ken Mattingly | journal = EE Times | publisher = UMB Tech | access-date = 2021-02-10 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200817230314/https://www.eetimes.com/power-engineer-video-interview-with-apollo-astronaut-ken-mattingly/ | archive-date = 2020-08-17 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.eetimes.com/power-engineer-video-interview-with-apollo-astronaut-ken-mattingly/}}</ref>。宇航员按亚伦等人命令启动指令舱，过程基本顺利。克兰兹事后表示，三名宇航员都曾是试飞员，心理素质过硬，能够在面临生命危险的情境下从容应对，所以才能全部生还。<ref name="Cass 3" />

宇航员长时间忍受严寒而且休息不足，可能导致再入前不能准时启动各部件。飞行控制中心在任务第133小时同意洛弗尔全面启动登月舱升温，包括启动登月舱导航计算机。计算机打开后洛弗尔便能导航瞄准并校准登月舱[[惯性测量单元|惯性测量单元]]。指令舱计算机按与登月舱正常设置程序相反的顺序校准，登月舱计算机掌握位置和方位信息，减少重启过程步骤，提升[[阿波罗主制导、导航与控制系统|阿波罗主制导、导航与控制系统]]控制再入的精度。<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/25day6-thelastcoursecorrection.html | title = Apollo Flight Journal: Day 6 Part 4 | publisher = NASA | access-date = 2021-09-12 | archive-date = 2022-01-18 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220118020508/https://www.history.nasa.gov/afj/ap13fj/25day6-thelastcoursecorrection.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>

=== 再入与溅落 ===
阿波罗13号精确切入地球轨道，但航天器仍然缓慢偏离航向，需要校正。登月舱在下降级推进系统点火进入自由返回轨道后关闭，地面控制人员要求宇航员利用地球上的昼夜分隔线导航，这种导航方式虽在航空航天局的地球轨道任务实践，但从未在月球任务返航时用过。<ref name="Cass 3" />任务第105小时18分42秒，下降级推进系统点火并保持14秒，把再入飞行路径角度带回安全范围，此后又在137小时40分13秒使用登月舱[[反推力系统|反推力系统]]再次点火并保持21.5秒。宇航员在不到半小时后抛弃服务舱，从而首度看到事故损失情况并拍照。据宇航员汇报，服务舱外部整块面板不知所踪，液氧罐上的燃料电池倾斜，高增益天线受损，大量碎片四处飘散。<ref name="Orloff-Harland-2006" />{{rp|370–371}}海斯还看到服务舱发动机喷管很可能损伤，证明克兰兹此前不动用服务推进系统的决定正确<ref name="Cass 3" />。
[[File:Apollo13_splashdown.jpg|thumb]]

接下来众人需要确保登月舱在适当时机与指令舱分离，保障再入时两舱的安全间隔。登月舱正常情况应在月球轨道抛弃，用服务舱的反推力系统将服务与指令舱拉走，但阿波罗13号的服务舱此时已经抛弃。制作登月舱的[[格鲁门公司|格鲁门公司]]派出[[多伦多大学|多伦多大学]]工程师研究组，由资深科学家[[伯纳德·埃特金|伯纳德·埃特金]]带队计算分离两舱所需气压。宇航员落实埃特金一行提出的方案后解决问题。<ref name="G&M">{{cite news | title = Bernard Etkin helped avert Apollo 13 tragedy | newspaper = The Globe and Mail | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200815090834/https://www.theglobeandmail.com/technology/science/bernard-etkin-helped-avert-apollo-13-tragedy/article19735265/#dashboard/follows/ | archive-date = 2020-08-15 | url = https://www.theglobeandmail.com/technology/science/bernard-etkin-helped-avert-apollo-13-tragedy/article19735265/#dashboard/follows/ | access-date = 2021-02-10}}</ref>登月舱再入地球大气层后烧毁，残余部分掉入大海<ref name="LM-ALSEP" /><ref name="impact">{{cite web | website = NASA Space Science Data Coordinated Archive | url = https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/planetary/lunar/apollo_impact.html | title = Impact Sites of Apollo LM Ascent and SIVB Stages | access-date = 2021-02-10 | archive-date = 2020-12-21 | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201221010413/https://nssdc.gsfc.nasa.gov/planetary/lunar/apollo_impact.html}}</ref>。美国原子能委员会要求尽可能避免航天器上计划用于放射性同位素热电机SNAP-27的二氧化钚污染环境，阿波罗13号的最后一次中途校正达成目标，核燃料罐落入深度名列前茅的太平洋[[汤加海沟|汤加海沟]]，一直沉到约万米深的海底。事后直升机测量没有发现放射物泄露。<ref name="Cass 3" />

再入期间，指令舱周围的电离层通常会引起四分钟通讯中断。阿波罗13号的再入角度很浅，通讯中断超过预期达到六分钟，地面人员一度担心指令舱防热大底损毁。<ref>{{cite magazine | title = Did Ron Howard exaggerate the reentry scene in the movie Apollo 13? | first = Joe | last = Pappalardo | access-date = 2021-02-10 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20201111201005/https://www.airspacemag.com/need-to-know/did-ron-howard-exaggerate-the-reentry-scene-in-the-movie-apollo-13-17639496/ | publisher = [[史密森尼学会|Smithsonian Institution]] | url = https://www.airspacemag.com/need-to-know/did-ron-howard-exaggerate-the-reentry-scene-in-the-movie-apollo-13-17639496/ | magazine = Air & Space/Smithsonian | location = Washington, D.C. | date = 2007-05-01 | dead-url = no | archive-date = 2020-11-11}}</ref>。恢复无线电通信后，“奥德赛”安全溅落南太平洋，溅落点在{{Coord|21|38|24|S|165|21|42|W|type:event|name=阿波罗13号溅落}}<ref name="Mission-Report-1970">{{cite book | url = https://ntrs.nasa.gov/api/citations/19710003598/downloads/19710003598.pdf | author = Mission Evaluation Team | id = MSC-02680 | location = Houston, Texas | date = 1970-09 | publisher = NASA Manned Spacecraft Center | title = Apollo 13 Mission Report | access-date = 2021-02-10 | archive-date = 2020-07-26 | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200726072334/https://ntrs.nasa.gov/archive/nasa/casi.ntrs.nasa.gov/19710003598.pdf | format = PDF}}</ref>{{rp|1-2}}，[[美屬薩摩亞|美屬薩摩亞]]东南方向，距搜救船硫磺岛号两栖攻击舰6.5公里<ref name="Orloff-Harland-2006" />{{rp|371}}。三名宇航员非常疲累，但除海斯因饮水不足导致严重尿道感染外，另外两人身体良好<ref name="Cortright-1975" />{{rp|262–263}}。在舰上过夜后，三人次日飞抵美屬薩摩亞[[帕果帕果|帕果帕果]]，随后又飞往夏威夷接受[[理查德·尼克松|理查德·尼克松]]总统颁发的美国平民最高荣誉：[[總統自由勳章|總統自由勳章]]<ref>{{cite news | access-date = 2021-02-10 | url = https://www.newspapers.com/clip/39764154/heroes-of-apollo-13-welcomed-by/ | title = Heroes of Apollo 13 Welcomed by President and Loved Ones | agency = Associated Press | newspaper = The Philadelphia Enquirer | location = Philadelphia, Pennsylvania | date = 1970-04-19 | via = Newspapers.com | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200814202138/https://www.newspapers.com/clip/39764154/heroes-of-apollo-13-welcomed-by/ | page = 1 | archive-date = 2020-08-14 | dead-url = no}}</ref>。宇航员在夏威夷过夜后飞回休斯顿<ref name="Mission-Report-1970" />{{rp|10-5}}。

尼克松总统前往檀香山中途先到休斯顿向阿波罗13号任务控制组人员颁发总统自由勋章<ref name="nixon">{{cite web | title = Behind the Scenes of Apollo 13 | access-date = 2021-02-10 | date = 2016-04-11 | url = https://www.nixonfoundation.org/2016/04/behind-scenes-apollo-13/ | website = Richard Nixon Foundation | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200929183137/https://www.nixonfoundation.org/2016/04/behind-scenes-apollo-13/ | dead-url = no | archive-date = 2020-09-29}}</ref>。他原计划颁给[[美國國家航空暨太空總署署長及副署長列表|航空航天局局长]][[托马斯·奥滕·潘恩|托马斯·潘恩]]，是潘恩建议授予任务控制组<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/documents/remarks-presenting-the-presidential-medal-freedom-apollo-13-mission-operations-team | title = Remarks on Presenting the Presidential Medal of Freedom to Apollo 13 Mission Operations Team in Houston. | publisher = The American Presidency Project | access-date = 2021-02-10 | dead-url = no | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200811005405/https://www.presidency.ucsb.edu/documents/remarks-presenting-the-presidential-medal-freedom-apollo-13-mission-operations-team | archive-date = 2020-08-11}}</ref>。

== 公众和媒体关注 ==
[[File:Jim_Lovell_newspaper.jpg|thumb]]和潘恩博士前来接见，媳妇玛丽莲和弗莱德的老婆玛丽、还有单身汉杰克的父母都在一旁，这下他身边终于不像以往那样老站着某个空姐啦。|source = 吉姆·洛弗尔<ref name="Cortright-1975" />{{rp|262–263}}|style=padding: 15px; margin: 0;text-align: justify;}}]]

阿波罗13号事故令世界各地重新燃起对阿波罗计划的关注，数以百万计的民众通过电视关注事态进展。四艘苏联舰船开往溅落地点，以便在需要时伸出援手，<ref name="NASA-1970" />{{rp|15}}其他国家表示愿意派船协助溅落其他地点的航天器<ref name="Benson-Faherty-1979" />{{rp|489–494}}尼克松取消预定日程致电宇航员家属，乘车前往航空航天局位于马里兰州[[绿带城|绿带城]]的[[戈达德太空飞行中心|戈达德太空飞行中心]]，了解航天器追踪和通讯协调情况<ref name="NASA-1970" />{{rp|15}}。

公众对搜救过程的关注同样超出以往，包括首次登月的阿波罗11号。除世界各地的头条新闻外，人们围在电视机前了解最新进展，电视台中断常规节目发布公告。教皇[[保祿六世|保祿六世]]带领一万名会众祈祷宇航员安全返回，印度宗教节庆活动期间的祈祷人数更达十万。<ref name="Chaikin-1998" />{{rp|316}}[[美国参议院|美国参议院]]4月14日通过决议，呼吁企业当晚九点暂停作业，方便雇员祈祷<ref name="NASA-1970" />{{rp|15}}。

估计有四千万美国人收看阿波罗13号溅落实况，[[美國三大電視網|美國三大電視網]]现场直播；电视直播长达六个半小时，另有约三千万人至少观看部分实况。其他国家和地区的观众人数更多，[[杰克·古尔德|杰克·古尔德]]在《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》刊文指出，阿波罗13号“虽然差点变成悲惨的灾难，但却很可能比又一次成功登月更有力地团结全世界，表达世界人民的相互关注。”<ref>{{cite news | last = Gould | first = Jack | newspaper = The New York Times | date = 1970-04-18 | page = 59 | title = TV: Millions of viewers end vigil for Apollo 13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200723051039/https://www.nytimes.com/1970/04/18/archives/tv-millions-of-viewers-end-vigil-for-apollo-13-unusual-color.html?searchResultPosition=8 | archive-date = 2020-07-23 | dead-url = no | url = https://www.nytimes.com/1970/04/18/archives/tv-millions-of-viewers-end-vigil-for-apollo-13-unusual-color.html}}</ref>

== 调查和反响 ==

=== 审查委员会 ===
[[File:Apollo13_tank2.jpg|thumb]]

宇航员返回后，航空航天局局长潘恩和副局长[[乔治·洛|乔治·洛]]任命审查委员会调查事故。委员会由航空航天局[[兰利研究中心|兰利研究中心]]主任[[埃德加·科特赖特|埃德加·科特赖特]]牵头，还有包括阿姆斯特朗在内的七名成员。{{refn|group="注"|另外六人分别是：航空航天局总部局长助理罗伯特·阿纳特，戈达德太空飞行中心主任约翰·克拉克、美国空军太空总部主任小沃尔特·赫德里克准将，太空科学与应用办公室副行政工程主任助理文森特·约翰逊，美国原子能委员会－国家航空航天局核推进办公室主任[[米尔顿·克莱因|米尔顿·克莱因]]，艾姆斯研究中心主任[[汉斯·马克|汉斯·马克]]<ref name="Accident report" />{{rp|1-1–1-4}}。}}委员会6月15日向潘恩递交最终报告<ref name="Accident report" />{{rp|15}}，称故障源于服务舱二号液氧罐<ref name="Accident report" />{{rp|4-36}}。罐内搅拌风扇导线上的[[聚四氟乙烯|聚四氟乙烯]]绝缘层受损导致[[短路|短路]]，随即引燃绝缘层。火苗令罐内压力迅速上升、罐顶破损，液氧迅速气化并膨胀，与燃烧产物充满四号托架的燃料电池舱。逸出气体很可能足以吹开四号托架的铝制面板，附近绝缘材料的燃烧产物令压力进一步增大。面板脱落导致气罐暴露并扑灭火焰，很可能正是脱落面板打到旁边的高增益天线，令航天器与地球的通讯中断1.8秒。<ref name="Orloff-Harland-2006" />{{rp|372–373}}服务舱与指令舱间并非密闭，如果整个服务舱有充足时间像四号托架一样加压，指令舱防热大底受压，指令舱与服务舱最后会相互分离。报告质疑氧气瓶这样至关重要的东西内部为何要用聚四氟乙烯、铝这类易燃材料。<ref name="Accident report" />{{rp|5-6–5-7, 5-12–5-13}}委员会认为，没有证据表明事故是因其他原因引起<ref name="Accident report" />{{rp|4-37}}。
